  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Clans/Yohra.jpg",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You invoke your innate ability to self-destruct, releasing a wave of explosive force in the area immediately around you.</p><p>All creatures within range must make a Constitution saving throw with a penalty equal to half the result of your hit die, taking unreducible force damage equal to your maximum hit points + half of your maximum chakra points, as well as being Dazed for the next minute, Weakened, and knocked prone on a failure, or half as much and only being knocked prone on a success.</p><p>At the conclusion of this jutsu, your hit points are set to 1, armor you are wearing of Superior or lower quality is atomized, and you become unconscious. While unconscious in this way, you cannot regain consciousness or be healed for the next minute, after which you can only be healed up to half of your maximum hit points until you complete a long rest.</p><p>While you are unconscious in this way, your Pod acts autonomously in your place, and allied creatures can use it to perform YoRHa Hijutsu that require it as a component as if they knew them, ignoring the YoRHa weapon component.</p><p><strong>At Higher Ranks:</strong> For each rank you cast this jutsu above B-Rank, increase the cost of this jutsu by 3 and the hit die spent and applied to the penalty by 1.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
